    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <head>250. Telegram From the Chief of the Military Assistance Advisory Group in
                    Vietnam (<persName corresp="#p_MGLGLC1" type="from">McGarr</persName>) to the
                    Secretary of Defense’s Deputy Assistant for Special Operations (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LCEG1" type="to">Lansdale</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d250fn1">Source: Washington National Records Center, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 330, <persName corresp="#p_LCEG1"
                            >Lansdale</persName> Papers: <gloss target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 63 A
                        1803, Vietnam Correspondence 1960. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1960-11-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1960</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_SGN1">SGN</gloss> 252. Thanks for your most helpful
                        information.<note n="2" xml:id="d250fn2">Not further identified.</note> I
                    had already called <persName corresp="#p_THUAN1">Thuan</persName> and making
                        [<hi rend="italic">made</hi>] strong representation and he took up with
                    president. He called me today—Sunday—our time—and said <persName
                        corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> had agreed to place Civil Guard under
                        <gloss target="#t_VN1">VN</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss> for operational control also. Now awaiting
                    promised change in decree. This information not yet given country team. Your
                    help appreciated. Best not known by ambassador as may be misunderstood.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
